<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="97" type="comments">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="97">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="97">
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
<taxonomicName authority="K.Romaschenko, 2019" authorityName="K.Romaschenko" authorityYear="2019" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Eriosella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eriosella caduca" order="Poales" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caduca">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">Eriosella caduca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is thought to be a hybrid between 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Eriocoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eriocoma hymenoides" order="Poales" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hymenoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">Eriocoma hymenoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barkworth" authorityYear="1990" baseAuthorityName="Trin." class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Nassella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Nassella viridula" order="Poales" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="viridula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">Nassella viridula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It can be separated from 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. hymenoides" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" rank="species" species="hymenoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">E. hymenoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having shorter hairs on the lemma and panicles with ascending branches (not divergent), and from 
<taxonomicName genus="N." lsidName="N. viridula" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" rank="species" species="viridula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">N. viridula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having longer lemma hairs, paleas 2/3-3/4 as long as the lemma, and readily deciduous lemmatal awns (
<bibRefCitation author="Barkworth, ME" editor="Barkworth, ME" journalOrPublisher="Oxford Universtiy Press, New York" pageId="20" pageNumber="109" pagination="109 - 186" refId="B3" refString="Barkworth, ME, 2007. 10. Stipeae Dumort. In: Barkworth, ME, Capels, KM, Long, S, Anderton, LK, Piep, MB, Eds., Magnoliophyta: Commelinidae (in part): Poaceae, part 1. Oxford Universtiy Press, New York: 109 - 186" title="10. Stipeae Dumort." volumeTitle="Magnoliophyta: Commelinidae (in part): Poaceae, part 1." year="2007">Barkworth 2007</bibRefCitation>
). Another species similar to 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
<taxonomicName authority="K.Romaschenko, 2019" authorityName="K.Romaschenko" authorityYear="2019" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Eriosella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eriosella caduca" order="Poales" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caduca">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">Eriosella caduca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Eriocoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eriocoma bloomeri" order="Poales" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bloomeri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">Eriocoma bloomeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the latter species has glabrous sheaths, shorter ligules, 5-veined lemmas, awns with a sub-plumose lower section below the bend, and anthers with more numerous apical hairs (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1002/j.1537-2197.1943.tb14731.x" author="Johnson, BL" journalOrPublisher="Smithsonian Contributions to Botany" pageId="21" pageNumber="110" refId="B19" refString="Johnson, BL, Rogler, GA, 1943. A cyto-taxonomic study of an intergeneric hybrid between Oryzopsis hymenoides and Stipa viridula. American Journal of Botany 30(1): 49-56. https://doi.org/10.1002/j.1537-2197.1943.tb14731.x" title="A cyto-taxonomic study of an intergeneric hybrid between Oryzopsis hymenoides and Stipa viridula. American Journal of Botany 30 (1): 49 - 56." url="https://doi.org/10.1002/j.1537-2197.1943.tb14731.x" year="1943">Johnson and Rogler 1943</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
